# bmad-create-story.patch — guards for bmad-create-story/SKILL.md
# Validated against BMAD-METHOD 6.8.0 on 2026-05-28.
#
# Five guards wrap every local-write site so they fire only when
# tracking_system == 'file-system'. When tracking_system != 'file-system',
# control defers to the tracking adapter (lnr-tracking-adapter for Linear).
#
# Guard 1: Step 1 — epic-status update inside the user-input block (6-space indent).
# Guard 2: Step 1 — epic-status update inside the fallthrough block (4-space indent).
# Guard 3: Step 5 — story-file initialization + template-output block.
# Guard 4: Step 6 — "Save story document unconditionally".
# Guard 5: Step 6 — sprint-status.yaml update block (inside <check if="sprint status file exists">).

# Guard 1: Step 1 (user-input block) — epic-status update pair inside <check if="this is first story...">.
# Anchors on the two write actions with 6-space indent (unique due to indentation difference vs Guard 2).
GUARD_START
ANCHOR_BEGIN
      <action>If epic status is "backlog" → update to "in-progress"</action>
      <action>If epic status is "contexted" (legacy status) → update to "in-progress" (backward compatibility)</action>
ANCHOR_END
REPLACE_BEGIN
      <check if="{workflow.tracking_system}=='file-system'">
        <!-- bmad-linear-patch v0.2.0 -->
        <action>If epic status is "backlog" → update to "in-progress"</action>
        <action>If epic status is "contexted" (legacy status) → update to "in-progress" (backward compatibility)</action>
      </check>
      <check if="{workflow.tracking_system}!='file-system'">
        <!-- bmad-linear-patch v0.2.0 -->
        <action>Defer to {workflow.tracking_adapter} for epic status updates.</action>
      </check>
REPLACE_END
GUARD_END

# Guard 2: Step 1 (fallthrough block) — epic-status update pair inside <check if="this is first story...">.
# Anchors on the two write actions with 4-space indent (unique due to indentation difference vs Guard 1).
GUARD_START
ANCHOR_BEGIN
    <action>If epic status is "backlog" → update to "in-progress"</action>
    <action>If epic status is "contexted" (legacy status) → update to "in-progress" (backward compatibility)</action>
ANCHOR_END
REPLACE_BEGIN
